---
description: README tone—concise, human-readable, senior-engineer audience
globs:
  - "README.md"
alwaysApply: false
---

**Audience:** senior engineers (CLI, builds, VCS, reading code—skip hand-holding).

- **Voice:** direct English; outcome first; tradeoffs and limits when non-obvious. One strong
  example beats many weak ones; prefer real repo commands/paths when useful.
- **Shape:** clear `##` / `###`, fenced code with language tags, small tables for dense reference.
  Wrap prose near **100** columns when it stays readable.
- **Substance:** what / why / how for adoptable features; copy-pastable invocations or schema;
  note defaults, validation, failures only where it matters. No long tutorials unless the repo is
  one.
